  "title": "Food Packer",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Overview:</strong><br>\nWe are seeking a detail-oriented and efficient Food Packer with kitchen experience to join our team. The ideal candidate will be responsible for packing food products for shipment, ensuring all items are accurately labeled and meet our quality standards. Additionally, they will alternate between cutting protein, vegetables, and marinating as needed. This role requires a strong focus on safety, efficiency, and teamwork.</p>\n<p><strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Pack products in accordance with company guidelines and safety standards.</li>\n  <li>Inspect items for quality and completeness before packing.</li>\n  <li>Label packages clearly and accurately for shipping.</li>\n  <li>Assist in cutting protein, vegetables and marinating work.</li>\n  <li>Maintain a clean and organized work area.</li>\n  <li>Assist with inventory management and stock replenishment as needed.</li>\n  <li>Communicate effectively with team members and supervisors.</li>\n  <li>Follow all safety procedures and protocols to ensure a safe working environment.</li>\n  <li>Participate in training and development programs as required.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Qualifications:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Previous experience in a packing or similar role is preferred but not required</li>\n  <li>Attention to detail and high level of accuracy</li>\n  <li>Ability to work independently and as part of a team</li>\n  <li>Good physical condition with the ability to stand, bend, and lift items as needed</li>\n  <li>Positive attitude and reliable work ethics</li>\n  <li>Food Hygiene Certificate is required</li>\n  <li>Working hours - 9am to 6pm.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Stovve Foods (S) Pte Ltd is an equal-opportunity employer and encourages applications from all qualified individuals.</p>",
